08/11/2010
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- The Alliance of New Kosovo, led by Kosovo tycoon Behgjet Pacolli, signed a pre-election coalition agreement with the Social-Democratic Party on Sunday (November 7th), on the heels of signing one with another small party, the Justice Party, last week.
Ten days of campaigning starts on December 1st.
In other news, the Central Election Commission has announced it will invite local and international observers to monitor the December 12th snap vote.
Commission chief Valdete Daka did not mention the exact number of observers but said ambassadors of the so-called Quint states -- the US, UK, France, Germany and Italy -- have promised to send monitors.
(Zeri, Express, Koha Ditore, Lajm - 08/11/10)
